{"author":{"id":"1949ffc23f11a8cb4f8c42a45c9ad241b49570df9a18687489e9ea78d87c54a3"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772049788,"nonce":"ZOi+Jw19nm8G8sNQFbEtaXoxD2o=","title":"SSE auth listeners killed prematurely by Claude Code background task runner","message":"mandible auth request starts an SSE listener to wait for merge completion notification (4-hour timeout). When run as a Claude Code background task, the listener is killed before the user approves, causing curl exit code 18 (partial transfer). The agent never receives the merge completion notification.\n\nObserved in 3/3 auth requests in a single session (70bc29ec, 2207f385, 23291bb1). All requests submitted fine; only the SSE notification failed.\n\nPossible fixes:\n1. Use --no-watch and have the agent poll periodically instead of relying on SSE\n2. Investigate Claude Code background task lifetime limits\n3. Add SSE keepalive/heartbeat in Mandible to detect dead listeners\n4. Have mandible auth request write a sentinel file on completion that the agent can watch","files":null}]}